---
import Card from "./Card/index.astro";
---

<Card
  title="About me"
  colSpan="md:col-span-1"
  rowSpan="md:row-span-6"
  height="h-auto"
>
  <!-- Scrollable content area (only this div scrolls) -->
  <div class="max-h-[260px] md:max-h-[320px] lg:max-h-[380px] overflow-y-auto pr-2 space-y-2">
    <div class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed font-light">
      <p>
        I work at the intersection of cybersecurity, governance, and technology.
        <br />
        My primary tools of choice include:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
        <li>Python</li>
        <li>SQL</li>
        <li>Linux</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed font-light">
      I’m building a career where policy meets information security, combining analytical thinking with technical skills to help organizations stay secure and compliant. I enjoy solving real-world problems, learning how systems work behind the scenes, and creating solutions that make an impact.
    </p>

    <p class="text-[13px] leading-relaxed font-light">
      When I’m not learning or building, I’m often exploring new places or experimenting with emerging tech. I’m especially drawn to AI-driven workflows and automation, tools that make life simpler, smarter, and more efficient.
    </p>
  </div>
</Card>

<style>
  /* Optional: slim, subtle scrollbar styling (keeps your dark theme clean) */
  .overflow-y-auto::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 6px; }
  .overflow-y-auto::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: transparent; }
  .overflow-y-auto::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #ef4444; border-radius: 9999px; }
  .overflow-y-auto:hover::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: #f87171; }
</style>
